    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-04-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-04-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="482"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d482">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Taylor</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-04-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 23, 1897</hi>
                        </date>. (Received Mar. 7.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 686.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to Department’s telegrams of January 22
                    and March 1 and to my Nos. 636, of January-29, and 655, of March 3, of the
                    present year, relative to certain American citizens arrested in Cuba, I have the
                    honor to inform you that I have received a note from the minister for foreign
                    affairs, informing me officially that the American citizen Jose Gonzales
                    Curbelo, one of the prisoners named in the first-mentioned telegram, was placed
                    at liberty on the 30th of last March.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hannis Taylor.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
